                                        <depth unit="cm">16</depth>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.fragmentary"/>
                            </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Text covers whole of remaining fragments, with no additional room within entabulature at top and bottom. Whilst there is a break in "orname[n]-" in line 5, that it is finished in the surviving portion of line 6 (rather than being lost in the break to the left), suggests that the inscription was centred on the stone and that we have lost only 5–7 characters to the left.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Text is straight, relatively neat, and consistently spaced. Tall "T"s in line 3 in "Pontif", line 5 in "et" and line 6 in "tis". Tall "I" in line 4, final "I" in "Aeternitati". Interpuncts are relatively regular throughout.</p>
